<TITLE> Strong quake shakes Chittagong, southeast towns </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Nov 7 (bdnews24.com)  A strong earthquake jolted the southeast region of the country Wednesday afternoon, Met officials said. Farah Diba of the Meteorological Department told bdnews24.com that the quake measuring 6.0 on the Richter scale shook Chittagong, Cox's Bazaar, Feni and Khagrachhari, Rangamati, Bandarban and Noakhali at around 1:10pm. The quake was centred 70km southeast off the Chittagong Seismic Observation Centre. "It was a strong earthquake," Samarendra Karmaker, director of the Meteorological Department, told bdnews24.com. No news of serious damage to property or infrastructure came in but at least 10 were injured when people scrambled to run out of the buildings. bdnews24.com Chittagong correspondent said the tremor spread panic among the people who ran out to the streets from their homes. The injured were admitted to Chittagong Medical College Hospital, said sub-inspector Md Joynal, duty officer of the hospital police post. Of the injured three were identified as Haider Ali, 45, of Bayezid Bostami Road, Shah Alam, 26, employee of Delta Life Insurance Company of Agrabad and Sifat, a student of Chittagong College. Haque Super Market, a six-storey building at Bahaddarhat slanted, locals said, but Chandgaon Police Station chief Mokfuber Rahman said there was no casualty. Many contacted their families from their work after the quake to enquire about their wellbeing. Newspaper offices were busy receiving phones enquiring about accidents, if any. Kabir Hossain Sujan, a resident of Agrabad, told bdnews24.com their six-storey building developed cracks and the furniture were trembling for a few seconds. bdnews24.
